The paper focuses on using machine learning techniques, specifically deep reinforcement learning and reservoir computing, to address the challenges of distributed dynamic spectrum access. This falls under the intersection of several CS sub-categories, including machine learning (cs.LG), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), systems and control (cs.SY), and information theory (cs.IT). However, given the emphasis on machine learning and reinforcement learning, cs.LG is the most likely sub-category, followed by cs.NI and cs.AI.
